"""
TRUST SCORE FIX - PRODUCTION READY VERSION v3.0
================================================

PROBLEM IDENTIFIED
------------------
trust_score was read from the caller's event payload, allowing any authenticated
caller to set their own trust level. This is the Unverified Context Vulnerability:
the adversary controls their own prior probability of safety.

ATTACK SCENARIO (CONFIRMED IN AUDIT)
------------------------------------
Before fix: penalty = severity_penalty * caller_supplied_trust_score
  → Attacker submits {"trust_score": 0.1}
  → Critical event (0.20 penalty) becomes 0.02 (90% reduction)
  → After 20 events, stability drops only to 0.60 (should have hit 0.0/Critical)
  → System remains blind to ongoing critical attack

FIX ARCHITECTURE
----------------
Remove trust_score from the event payload entirely. Assign it server-side based
on verified API key identity, BEFORE the event reaches handle_demo_request().

THREE-PART IMPLEMENTATION
-------------------------
  1. TrustRegistry      — Maps API keys to trust levels (server-side only)
  2. get_trust_score()  — Replaces event.get("trust_score", 1.0)
  3. Payload validator  — Rejects any event that includes trust_score field
"""

